   <pbcoreTitle titleType="Title">The Great American Footrace</pbcoreTitle>
   <pbcoreDescription descriptionType="Program">Facing scorching temperatures, 19-year-old Andy Payne, a small-town Cherokee boy, takes home the gold after winning a grueling 3,422-mile foot race designed to bring attention to the newly constructed Route 66 Highway. The race recounted in this Emmy-nominated film became one of the wildest promotion schemes in history, allowing Andy to win enough money to marry his girl and keep the family farm.</pbcoreDescription>
